# Responsive Design Standards

## 1. Mobile-First Approach
Always define the base style for mobile and scale up for larger screens:
```tsx
// ✅ Correct: Mobile-first
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">

// ❌ Wrong: Desktop-first
<div className="grid grid-cols-4 md:grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-1">
```

## 2. Container Standards

### Graphs & Charts
Always use `<ResponsiveContainer>` with a fixed parent height:
```tsx
<div className="h-[250px] sm:h-[300px] w-full min-w-0">
    <ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height="100%">
        {/* Chart content */}
    </ResponsiveContainer>
</div>
```

### Tables
Always wrap tables in `overflow-x-auto` to prevent horizontal overflow:
```tsx
<div className="overflow-x-auto">
    <table className="w-full">
        {/* Table content */}
    </table>
</div>
```

### Page Containers
Use consistent max-width and padding:
```tsx
<div className="w-full max-w-screen-xl mx-auto px-4 py-6 sm:py-8">
    {/* Page content */}
</div>
```

## 3. Touch Targets
Buttons and inputs must be at least 44px height on mobile for accessibility:
```tsx
// ✅ Correct: Adequate touch target
<Button className="h-11 sm:h-10">Click Me</Button>

// Form inputs should have sufficient padding
<Input className="py-3 sm:py-2" />
```

## 4. Layouts
Use `flex-col` on mobile and `flex-row` on desktop for navigation/headers:
```tsx
<div className="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between gap-4">
    <h1>Title</h1>
    <button>Action</button>
</div>
```

## 5. Typography Scaling
Scale text sizes responsively:
```tsx
<h1 className="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold">
<p className="text-xs sm:text-sm text-muted-foreground">
```

## 6. Icons & Spacing
Scale icons and spacing for mobile:
```tsx
<Icon className="h-5 w-5 sm:h-6 sm:w-6" />
<div className="p-3 sm:p-4 gap-3 sm:gap-4">
```

## 7. Cards & Components
Use responsive padding and rounded corners:
```tsx
<div className="p-3 sm:p-4 rounded-lg sm:rounded-xl">
```

## 8. Navigation
- Desktop: Horizontal navigation with dropdown menus
- Mobile: Hamburger menu with Sheet/Drawer slide-in
```tsx
// Desktop nav
<nav className="hidden md:flex items-center gap-2">

// Mobile trigger
<button className="md:hidden">
    <Menu />
</button>
```

## 9. Forms
Stack form fields vertically on mobile, side-by-side on desktop:
```tsx
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
    <Input name="firstName" />
    <Input name="lastName" />
</div>
```

## 10. Testing Breakpoints
Tailwind breakpoints to test:
- `sm`: 640px
- `md`: 768px
- `lg`: 1024px
- `xl`: 1280px
- `2xl`: 1536px
